This is QUIZZERA, a microservices EdTech platform.
Stack: Node.js, Express, MongoDB, Firebase, Next.js.
No Docker. Services run locally with concurrently and nodemon.
MongoDB runs locally on mongodb://localhost:27017.
Each service has its own database: quizzera_auth, quizzera_users, quizzera_taxonomy, quizzera_mcq, quizzera_exam.
Ports: gateway=3000, auth=3001, user=3002, taxonomy=3003, mcq=3004, exam=3005.
Node services use ES modules: package.json "type": "module", import/export, and include the .js extension in relative imports.
Each service is fully independent with its own DB connection and its own PORT.
Firebase handles identity only. MongoDB is the source of truth for role, plan, entitlement, accountStatus. onboardingCompleted and user preferences exist only in quizzera_users (user-service), not in quizzera_auth.
Never put business logic in routes. Always use controllers and a services layer.
Always validate request body before hitting Firebase or MongoDB.
Return consistent JSON: { success: true, data: {} } or { success: false, message: "" }.
Theme: black and white only. #111111 text, #FFFFFF bg, #F9F9F9 cards, #E5E5E5 borders.